# .env configuration for Delta Media Bot
# Notes:
# - Values are read as strings unless noted.
# - Defaults shown below are the script's internal defaults when a variable is unset.
# - Copy this file to '.env' and adjust values for your environment.

# =====================
# Sender whitelist (REQUIRED)
# =====================
# Comma-separated list of allowed Delta Chat addresses the bot will respond to.
RESPOND_TO=user1@example.com,user2@example.com

# =====================
# Output paths (inside the container)
# =====================
# Bind-mount these to host directories your media server (Plex / Jellyfin) reads.
#DOWNLOAD_DIR=/downloads
#AUDIO_DIR=/downloads-audio

# =====================
# Quality
# =====================
# Optional max video height (e.g. 1080, 2160). Empty = true best available.
#MAX_HEIGHT=

# Comma-separated subtitle language codes to embed as soft tracks. Empty = no subs.
# Auto-generated subs are never included.
#SUBTITLE_LANGS=en

# =====================
# Safety net
# =====================
# Per-job timeout in seconds (default 14400 = 4 hours).
#JOB_TIMEOUT=14400

# =====================
# YouTube bot-detection workaround
# =====================
# Passed verbatim to `yt-dlp --extractor-args`. The default tries multiple YouTube
# player clients to dodge "Sign in to confirm you're not a bot" errors. When YouTube
# changes the rules, tune this list (see https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/wiki/Extractors
# under "youtube"). Set to empty to use yt-dlp's defaults.
#YT_EXTRACTOR_ARGS=youtube:player_client=default,tv,web_safari

# =====================
# Optional: PO Token provider for YouTube
# =====================
# When set, the bot tells yt-dlp to fetch Proof-of-Origin tokens from a
# bgutil-ytdlp-pot-provider HTTP server. See README "Optional: PO Token provider"
# for how to run the sidecar container. Leave unset to disable.
# Example (sidecar reachable on the Docker host's IP at port 4416):
#BGUTIL_POT_PROVIDER_URL=http://bgutil-provider:4416

# =====================
# Optional: Cookies for login-required content
# =====================
# Path INSIDE the container to a Netscape-format cookies file. When set, the bot
# passes `--cookies <path>` to yt-dlp. Required for YouTube content that returns
# `LOGIN_REQUIRED` (most Shorts, age-restricted, region-locked, embedded).
# Bind-mount your cookies file into the container, e.g.:
#   -v /mnt/configs/yt-cookies.txt:/cookies/yt-cookies.txt:ro
# and set COOKIES_FILE to the in-container path. See README "Optional: Cookies"
# for the export workflow and ownership note.
#COOKIES_FILE=/cookies/yt-cookies.txt
